building.name: Cannon
building.description: Defensive building. Shoots cannonballs with deadly effect, but cannot target flying troops.

building.name: Mortar
building.description: Defensive building with a long range. Shoots big boulders that deal area damage, but cannot hit targets that get too close!

building.name: Tesla
building.description: Defensive building. Whenever it's not zapping the enemy, the power of Electrickery is best kept grounded.

building.name: Tombstone
building.description: Building that periodically spawns Skeletons to fight the enemy... and when destroyed, spawns 4 more Skeletons! Creepy!

spell.name: Rage
spell.description: Increases troop movement and attack speed. Buildings attack faster and summon troops quicker, too. Chaaaarge!

spell.name: Freeze
spell.description: Freezes and damages enemy troops and buildings, making them unable to move or attack. Everybody chill. Reduced damage to Crown Towers.

spell.name: Lightning
spell.description: Bolts of lightning damage and stun up to three enemy troops or buildings with the most hitpoints in the target area. Reduced damage to Crown Towers.

spell.name: Zap
spell.description: Zaps enemies, briefly stunning them and dealing damage inside a small radius. Reduced damage to Crown Towers.

spell.name: Poison
spell.description: Covers the area in a deadly toxin, damaging enemy troops and buildings over time. Yet somehow leaves the grass green and healthy. Go figure! Reduced damage to Crown Towers.

spell.name: Graveyard
spell.description: Surprise! It's a party. A Skeleton party, anywhere in the Arena. Yay!

spell.name: Tornado
spell.description: Drags enemy troops to its center while dealing damage over time, just like a magnet. A big, swirling, Tornado-y magnet.

spell.name: Clone
spell.description: Duplicates all friendly troops in the target area. Cloned troops are fragile, but pack the same punch as the original! Doesn't affect buildings.

spell.name: Earthquake
spell.description: Deals Damage per second to Troops and Crown Towers. Deals huge Building Damage! Does not affect flying units (it is an EARTHquake, after all).

characters.name: Knight
characters.description: A tough melee fighter. The Barbarian's handsome, cultured cousin. Rumor has it that he was knighted based on the sheer awesomeness of his mustache alone.

characters.name: Giant
characters.description: Slow but durable, only attacks buildings. A real one-man wrecking crew!

characters.name: Balloon
characters.description: As pretty as they are, you won't want a parade of THESE balloons showing up on the horizon. Drops powerful bombs and when shot down, crashes dealing area damage.

characters.name: Witch
characters.description: Summons Skeletons, shoots destructo beams, has glowing pink eyes that unfortunately don't shoot lasers.

characters.name: Golem
characters.description: Slow but durable, only attacks buildings. When destroyed, explosively splits into two Golemites and deals area damage!

characters.name: Valkyrie
characters.description: Tough melee fighter, deals area damage around her. Swarm or horde, no problem! She can take them all out with a few spins.

characters.name: Bomber
characters.description: Small, lightly protected skeleton who throws bombs. Deals area damage that can wipe out a swarm of enemies.

characters.name: Musketeer
characters.description: Don't be fooled by her delicately coiffed hair, the Musketeer is a mean shot with her trusty boomstick.

characters.name: Wizard
characters.description: The most awesome man to ever set foot in the Arena, the Wizard will blow you away with his handsomeness... and/or fireballs.

characters.name: Prince
characters.description: Don't let the little pony fool you. Once the Prince gets a running start, you WILL be trampled. Deals double damage once he gets charging.

characters.name: Princess
characters.description: This stunning Princess shoots flaming arrows from long range. If you're feeling warm feelings towards her, it's probably because you're on fire.

characters.name: Miner
characters.description: The Miner can burrow his way underground and appear anywhere in the Arena. It's not magic, it's a shovel. A shovel that deals reduced damage to Crown Towers.

characters.name: Bowler
characters.description: This big blue dude digs the simple things in life - Dark Elixir drinks and throwing rocks. His massive boulders roll through their target, hitting everything behind for a strike!

characters.name: Hunter
characters.description: He deals BIG damage up close - not so much at range. What he lacks in accuracy, he makes up for with his impressively bushy eyebrows.

characters.name: Fisherman
characters.description: His Ranged Attack can pull enemies towards him, and pull himself to enemy buildings. He's also mastered the ancient art of 'Fish Slapping'.

characters.name: Firecracker
characters.description: Shoots a firework that explodes upon impact, damaging the target and showering anything directly behind it with sparks. This is what happens when Archers get bored!
